  1. Plotting the budget against gross in popular American movies to see if there is a correlation.
return_on_budget <- data1 %>%
  filter(country == 'USA', num_user_for_reviews > 150, num_critic_for_reviews > 150) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=budget/100000, y=gross/100000)) %>%
  + geom_point(aes(color=imdb_score), alpha= 0.3) %>%
  + stat_smooth(method=loess) %>%
  + labs(title='Budget Efficiency', x="Budget (in hundred thousands of dollars)", y="Gross Revenue (in hundred of thousands of dollars)", color = "Score") %>%
  + theme_economist() %>%
  + theme(legend.key.size = unit(.3, "cm"))
